1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill Nos. 3068 & 3049, Page 1, Section A,
2 Line 6, by inserting after all of said section and line the following:
3
4 "43.265. There is hereby created in the state treasury the "Highway Patrol's Motor
5 Vehicle, Aircraft, and Watercraft Revolving Fund", which shall be administered by the
6 superintendent of the highway patrol. All funds received by the highway patrol from:
7 (1) Any source for purchase and maintenance of highway patrol motor vehicles,
8 watercraft, watercraft motors, and trailers;
9 (2) Any source for reimbursement of costs associated with the official use of highway
10 patrol vehicles;
11 (3) Any source for restitution for damage to or loss of a highway patrol vehicle or
12 aircraft;
13 (4) Any other source for the purchase and maintenance of highway patrol aircraft or
14 aircraft parts; and
15 (5) Government agencies for the reimbursement of costs associated with aircraft flights
16 flown on their behalf by the highway patrol;
17
18 shall be credited to the fund. The state treasurer is the custodian of the fund and shall approve
19 disbursements from the fund subject to appropriation and as provided by law and the constitution
20 of this state at the request of the superintendent of the highway patrol. The balances from this
21 fund shall be used for the purchase and maintenance of highway patrol motor vehicles, highway
22 patrol watercraft, watercraft motors, and trailers, highway patrol aircraft or aircraft parts and
23 operational costs. Prior to obligating any funds for the purchase of an individual unit that costs
24 in excess of [one] five hundred thousand dollars, the highway patrol shall receive a specific
25 appropriation from the general assembly for the particular purchase. Any unexpended balance in
26 the fund at the end of the fiscal year shall be exempt from the provisions of section 33.080
27 relating to the transfer of unexpended balances to the general revenue fund."; and
28
29 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
30 accordingly.
